---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const siteUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_SITE_URL || 'https://roadreadysafety.com';
const enrollUrl = '/courses/ny-ipirp';

const faqs = [
  {
    "q": "How often can I take defensive driving for points in New York?",
    "a": "Once every 18 months. The point reduction applies only to convictions from the 18 months before you complete the course."
  },
  {
    "q": "How often do I retake it for the insurance discount?",
    "a": "Every 36 months. The 10% discount lasts three years, so you retake an approved course before it lapses to keep it going."
  },
  {
    "q": "Why are there two different time periods?",
    "a": "They're two separate benefits with separate rules: 18 months governs point reduction, and 36 months governs the insurance discount. They run independently of each other."
  },
  {
    "q": "Can I renew the insurance discount with a clean record?",
    "a": "Yes. The insurance discount doesn't depend on having points — any licensed driver can retake the course every three years to keep the 10% reduction."
  }
];

const articleSchema = JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: "How Often Can You Take Defensive Driving in New York?",
  description: "Two clocks confuse everyone: you can use a New York course for point reduction once every 18 months, but you retake every 36 months to keep the insurance discount. Here's how they work.",
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Road Ready Safety' },
  publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Road Ready Safety', url: siteUrl },
  datePublished: '2026-06-12',
  dateModified: '2026-06-12',
  mainEntityOfPage: `${siteUrl}/new-york/how-often-can-you-take-it`,
});

const faqSchema = JSON.stringify({
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: faqs.map(f => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })),
});
---

<Layout
  title="How Often Can You Take Defensive Driving in New York? (18 vs 36 Months)"
  description="Two clocks confuse everyone: you can use a New York course for point reduction once every 18 months, but you retake every 36 months to keep the insurance discount. Here's how they work."
  keywords="how often defensive driving New York, 18 months point reduction NY, 36 months insurance discount, retake PIRP NY"
  url="/new-york/how-often-can-you-take-it"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={articleSchema} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={faqSchema} />
  </Fragment>
  <Header />

  <main class="bg-white">
    <article class="bg-white pb-16 lg:pb-24">
      <div class="max-w-[880px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-10 lg:pt-14">

        <p class="text-sm text-text-body mb-6" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">
          <a href="/" class="text-primary-deep font-medium hover:underline">Home</a>
          <span class="mx-2 text-text-subtle">›</span>
          <a href="/new-york" class="text-primary-deep font-medium hover:underline">New York Defensive Driving</a>
          <span class="mx-2 text-text-subtle">›</span>
          <span class="text-text">How often can you take it?</span>
        </p>

        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-[44px] font-bold text-primary-navy leading-tight tracking-[-0.02em] mb-6" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">
          How Often Can You Take Defensive Driving in New York?
        </h1>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-body text-base leading-7 mb-8" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">
          <p>There are two different clocks, and almost everyone mixes them up. For <strong>point reduction</strong>, you can use a course once every <strong>18 months</strong>. For the <strong>insurance discount</strong>, you retake every <strong>36 months</strong> to keep it going. They run independently.</p>
          <p>Here's how each one works so you time it right.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface-muted border border-border rounded-xl p-5 mb-10">
          <p class="text-sm text-text-body" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">This page is general information about New York PIRP (the Point &amp; Insurance Reduction Program), not legal or insurance advice. Confirm current rules with the NY DMV and your insurer.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">The 18-month clock (points)</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-body text-base leading-7 mb-10" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">
          <p>You can use a PIRP course to reduce points <strong>once in any 18-month period</strong>, and the reduction only applies to convictions from the 18 months before you finish the course.</p>
          <p>So if you took a course for point reduction recently, a second course won't reduce points again until 18 months have passed. See <a href="/new-york/does-defensive-driving-remove-points" class="text-primary-deep font-medium hover:underline">how point reduction works</a> for the details.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">The 36-month clock (insurance)</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-body text-base leading-7 mb-10" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">
          <p>The insurance discount lasts three years from completion. To keep the 10% in place, you take an approved course again <strong>every 36 months</strong>.</p>
          <p>This clock has nothing to do with points — you can renew the insurance discount even with a clean record. See <a href="/new-york/insurance-discount" class="text-primary-deep font-medium hover:underline">how the discount works</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">How to think about timing</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-body text-base leading-7 mb-10" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">
          <p>If you're taking the course mainly for insurance, just set a reminder for every three years. If you're taking it for points after a conviction, make sure 18 months have passed since your last point-reduction course.</p>
          <p>Many drivers simply retake every three years for the insurance discount, which also keeps a point-reduction course available whenever they happen to need it.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-8 mb-12">
          {faqs.map(item => (
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mb-2" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">{item.q}</h3>
              <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-7" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;" set:html={item.a} />
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">Keep your discount from lapsing</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-body text-base leading-7 mb-8" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">
          <p>If your three years are almost up, retaking an approved course keeps the 10% going. When you're ready, we'll point you to the New York online course.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mb-10">
          <a
            href={enrollUrl}
            class="inline-flex bg-primary hover:bg-primary-hover text-white h-[56px] px-8 rounded-[16px] text-lg font-semibold items-center justify-center no-underline"
            style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; box-shadow: 0px 10px 15px -3px rgba(17,23,34,0.08), 0px 4px 6px -4px rgba(17,23,34,0.05);"
          >
            See the New York Course →
          </a>
          <a
            href="/new-york"
            class="inline-flex h-[56px] px-8 border border-primary-deep text-primary-deep hover:bg-primary-deep hover:text-white rounded-[16px] text-lg font-semibold items-center justify-center no-underline transition-colors"
            style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;"
          >
            Back to the New York guide
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="pt-6 border-t border-border space-y-2" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">
          <p class="text-sm text-text-subtle">Road Ready Safety refers New York drivers to TicketSchool, a DMV-approved PIRP course sponsor, and may earn a commission. We are not the New York DMV or the course provider. This page is general information, not legal or insurance advice — confirm current rules with the NY DMV (dmv.ny.gov) and your insurer.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-subtle">Last updated June 12, 2026 — verified by the Road Ready Safety editorial team against the New York DMV PIRP pages (dmv.ny.gov).</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
